{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_MkJW2yrqJtTcbRSNq1YHyfHZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→schema: aidd.spec.v1\n     3→\n     4→# Core\n     5→status: draft\n     6→updated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\n     7→ticket: \"TST-001\"\n     8→slug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n     9→\n    10→owners:\n    11→  product: \"security-team\"\n    12→  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n    13→  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n    14→\n    15→sources:\n    16→  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n    17→  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n    18→  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n    19→  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n    20→\n    21→spec_pack:\n    22→  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n    23→  non_goals:\n    24→    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    25→    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    26→    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n    27→  constraints:\n    28→    - \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n    29→    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    30→    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    31→    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n    32→  decisions:\n    33→    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    34→    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n    35→    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    36→    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    37→    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n    38→  risks_top:\n    39→    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    40→    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    41→    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n    42→  links:\n    43→    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n    44→\n    45→iteration_decisions:\n    46→  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    47→    scope:\n    48→      - api_contract\n    49→      - data_model\n    50→      - tests\n    51→      - roll_out\n    52→      - observability\n    53→    decisions:\n    54→      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n    55→      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n    56→      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n    57→      - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    58→      - \"Q2: No existing RBAC - build from scratch [Interview: D]\"\n    59→    open_questions: []\n    60→\n    61→platforms:\n    62→  frontend:\n    63→    enabled: true\n    64→    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n    65→  backend:\n    66→    enabled: true\n    67→    stack_hint: \"Build from scratch - no existing RBAC (per interview Q2=D)\"\n    68→  mobile:\n    69→    enabled: false\n    70→    stack_hint: \"\"\n    71→\n    72→user_flows:\n    73→  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    74→    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    75→    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    76→    steps:\n    77→      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n    78→      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n    79→      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n    80→      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n    81→      - \"Frontend updates auth state without refresh\"\n    82→    edge_cases:\n    83→      - \"Insufficient admin permissions → 403 with audit log\"\n    84→      - \"WebSocket unavailable → graceful degradation\"\n    85→  - id: \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    86→    actors: [\"user\"]\n    87→    entrypoints: [\"POST/PUT/DELETE APIs\"]\n    88→    steps:\n    89→      - \"User attempts restricted action\"\n    90→      - \"RBAC middleware checks JWT claims\"\n    91→      - \"Access denied → 403 Forbidden\"\n    92→      - \"Attempt logged to audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\"\n    93→      - \"Frontend displays permission error\"\n    94→    edge_cases:\n    95→      - \"JWT token expired → 401 (not 403)\"\n    96→  - id: \"flow.live-session-update\"\n    97→    actors: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    98→    entrypoints: [\"WebSocket connection\"]\n    99→    steps:\n   100→      - \"User active in React app\"\n   101→      - \"Admin revokes role via API\"\n   102→      - \"WebSocket server broadcasts update\"\n   103→      - \"Redux store updates auth state\"\n   104→      - \"UI immediately hides restricted elements\"\n   105→    edge_cases:\n   106→      - \"Connection lost → exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   107→\n   108→ui_ux:\n   109→  screens:\n   110→    - \"Admin role management interface (existing)\"\n   111→    - \"Permission denied error display\"\n   112→  states:\n   113→    loading: [\"WebSocket connection status indicator\"]\n   114→    empty: []\n   115→    error: [\"403 permission denied message\", \"WebSocket connection error\"]\n   116→    partial_success: []\n   117→  accessibility:\n   118→    - \"Error messages must be screen-reader accessible\"\n   119→  i18n:\n   120→    - \"Permission error messages need i18n support\"\n   121→  analytics_events:\n   122→    - \"role_change_denied\"\n   123→    - \"permission_check_failed\"\n   124→\n   125→api_contract:\n   126→  - id: \"ALL POST/PUT/DELETE /*\"\n   127→    auth: \"JWT Bearer\"\n   128→    request:\n   129→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   130→      body_schema: {}\n   131→    response:\n   132→      success_schema: {}\n   133→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   134→      timeouts_ms: 5000\n   135→  - id: \"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"\n   136→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (admin only)\"\n   137→    request:\n   138→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   139→      body_schema:\n   140→        role: \"string\"\n   141→    response:\n   142→      success_schema:\n   143→        user_id: \"string\"\n   144→        new_role: \"string\"\n   145→        updated_at: \"timestamp\"\n   146→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"404 Not Found\", \"400 Bad Request\"]\n   147→      timeouts_ms: 3000\n   148→  - id: \"WS /ws/session\"\n   149→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (upgrade)\"\n   150→    request:\n   151→      content_type: \"N/A\"\n   152→      body_schema: {}\n   153→    response:\n   154→      success_schema:\n   155→        event: \"role_updated\"\n   156→        payload:\n   157→          user_id: \"string\"\n   158→          new_role: \"string\"\n   159→          timestamp: \"string\"\n   160→      error_codes: [\"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   161→      timeouts_ms: 30000\n   162→\n   163→data_model:\n   164→  entities:\n   165→    - name: \"audit_log\"\n   166→      fields:\n   167→        - \"id: UUID PK\"\n   168→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   169→        - \"action: ENUM(GRANT, REVOKE, DENIED)\"\n   170→        - \"target_resource: STRING\"\n   171→        - \"role_changes: JSONB\"\n   172→        - \"timestamp: TIMESTAMP\"\n   173→        - \"ip_address: INET\"\n   174→        - \"user_agent: STRING\"\n   175→    - name: \"user_sessions\"\n   176→      fields:\n   177→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   178→        - \"role: STRING\"\n   179→        - \"permissions: JSONB\"\n   180→        - \"last_updated: TIMESTAMP\"\n   181→  schema_changes:\n   182→    required: true\n   183→    notes: \"New audit_log table required; user_sessions cache table optional for performance\"\n   184→  versioning: \"backward\"\n   185→  idempotency: \"Role updates must be idempotent (same role set = no-op)\"\n   186→\n   187→tradeoffs:\n   188→  - topic: \"RBAC check caching strategy\"\n   189→    options:\n   190→      - name: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   191→        pros: [\"Fast (<10ms)\", \"Simple implementation\"]\n   192→        cons: [\"Stale data risk\", \"Per-node cache\"]\n   193→      - name: \"Redis distributed cache\"\n   194→        pros: [\"Consistent across nodes\", \"Configurable TTL\"]\n   195→        cons: [\"Network latency\", \"Additional infrastructure\"]\n   196→    decision: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   197→    rationale: \"Meet P95 <10ms latency requirement; accept eventual consistency for role changes via WebSocket push\"\n   198→  - topic: \"Session sync mechanism\"\n   199→    options:\n   200→      - name: \"WebSocket push\"\n   201→        pros: [\"Real-time updates\", \"Efficient\"]\n   202→        cons: [\"Connection management complexity\"]\n   203→      - name: \"Short polling\"\n   204→        pros: [\"Simple implementation\", \"No persistent connections\"]\n   205→        cons: [\"Higher latency\", \"Unnecessary load\"]\n   206→    decision: \"WebSocket push\"\n   207→    rationale: \"<5 second sync requirement demands WebSocket; polling would add unnecessary load\"\n   208→\n   209→risks:\n   210→  - risk: \"Performance impact from live RBAC checks on every request\"\n   211→    impact: \"high\"\n   212→    mitigation:\n   213→      - \"In-memory caching with TTL\"\n   214→      - \"Async audit logging\"\n   215→    detection:\n   216→      - \"RBAC latency P95 metrics\"\n   217→      - \"Alert if >10ms\"\n   218→  - risk: \"Session desync between backend and frontend\"\n   219→    impact: \"med\"\n   220→    mitigation:\n   221→      - \"WebSocket with heartbeat\"\n   222→      - \"Fallback to polling\"\n   223→    detection:\n   224→      - \"WebSocket connection metrics\"\n   225→      - \"Role mismatch logs\"\n   226→  - risk: \"Audit log storage growth\"\n   227→    impact: \"med\"\n   228→    mitigation:\n   229→      - \"Retention policy (90 days)\"\n   230→      - \"Archive to cold storage\"\n   231→    detection:\n   232→      - \"Storage usage monitoring\"\n   233→      - \"Growth rate alerts\"\n   234→  - risk: \"WebSocket connection instability\"\n   235→    impact: \"high\"\n   236→    mitigation:\n   237→      - \"Graceful degradation\"\n   238→      - \"Exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   239→    detection:\n   240→      - \"Connection uptime metrics\"\n   241→      - \"Error rate monitoring\"\n   242→\n   243→observability:\n   244→  logs:\n   245→    - \"RBAC check results (allowed/denied)\"\n   246→    - \"Audit log writes\"\n   247→    - \"WebSocket connection events\"\n   248→  metrics:\n   249→    - \"rbac_check_latency_p95\"\n   250→    - \"rbac_check_denied_total\"\n   251→    - \"audit_log_writes_total\"\n   252→    - \"websocket_connections_active\"\n   253→    - \"websocket_events_sent_total\"\n   254→  traces:\n   255→    - \"RBAC decision path\"\n   256→    - \"WebSocket message flow\"\n   257→  dashboards:\n   258→    - \"RBAC Performance Dashboard\"\n   259→    - \"Audit Log Activity\"\n   260→\n   261→roll_out:\n   262→  feature_flags:\n   263→    - name: \"rbac_live_enforcement\"\n   264→      description: \"Enable live RBAC checks on mutation APIs\"\n   265→    - name: \"websocket_session_sync\"\n   266→      description: \"Enable WebSocket session updates\"\n   267→  stages:\n   268→    - \"Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\"\n   269→    - \"Phase 2: WebSocket infrastructure\"\n   270→    - \"Phase 3: Frontend integration\"\n   271→    - \"Phase 4: E2E testing + performance validation\"\n   272→  rollback:\n   273→    - \"Disable feature flags\"\n   274→    - \"Revert to previous middleware version\"\n   275→\n   276→test_strategy:\n   277→  unit:\n   278→    scope:\n   279→      - \"RBAC middleware logic\"\n   280→      - \"JWT claims parsing\"\n   281→      - \"Audit log formatting\"\n   282→  integration:\n   283→    scope:\n   284→      - \"RBAC middleware + JWT integration\"\n   285→      - \"Audit log database writes\"\n   286→      - \"WebSocket connection handling\"\n   287→  contract:\n   288→    scope:\n   289→      - \"API response schemas\"\n   290→      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n   291→  e2e:\n   292→    scope:\n   293→      - \"Admin role change flow\"\n   294→      - \"Permission denied flow\"\n   295→      - \"Live session update flow\"\n   296→    critical_paths:\n   297→      - \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n   298→      - \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   299→      - \"flow.live-session-update\"\n   300→  test_data:\n   301→    fixtures:\n   302→      - \"Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions\"\n   303→      - \"Regular user with limited role\"\n   304→      - \"User with expired JWT\"\n   305→  environments:\n   306→    stage:\n   307→      - \"Integration test environment\"\n   308→      - \"Load test environment\"\n   309→\n   310→open_questions:\n   311→  blocker: []\n   312→  non_blocker:\n   313→    - \"What is the preferred audit log retention period beyond 90 days?\"\n   314→    - \"Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\"\n   315→\n   316→done_definition:\n   317→  acceptance_criteria_map:\n   318→    - ac: \"AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users\"\n   319→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   320→    - ac: \"AC-2: All role operations logged to audit_log\"\n   321→      test_coverage: \"integration audit_log writes\"\n   322→    - ac: \"AC-3: Frontend updates within 5 seconds of backend change\"\n   323→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.live-session-update\"\n   324→    - ac: \"AC-4: RBAC latency P95 <= 10ms at 1000 RPS\"\n   325→      test_coverage: \"load test validation\"\n   326→  manual_checks:\n   327→    - \"Verify WebSocket graceful degradation when connection lost\"\n   328→    - \"Verify audit logs do not contain sensitive data\"\n   329→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"ff39c298-e5a5-4ee6-ae00-3f54c36a238c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml","content":"---\nschema: aidd.spec.v1\n\n# Core\nstatus: draft\nupdated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\nticket: \"TST-001\"\nslug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n\nowners:\n  product: \"security-team\"\n  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n\nsources:\n  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n\nspec_pack:\n  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n  non_goals:\n    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n  constraints:\n    - \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n  decisions:\n    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n  risks_top:\n    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n  links:\n    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n\niteration_decisions:\n  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    scope:\n      - api_contract\n      - data_model\n      - tests\n      - roll_out\n      - observability\n    decisions:\n      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n      - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n      - \"Q2: No existing RBAC - build from scratch [Interview: D]\"\n    open_questions: []\n\nplatforms:\n  frontend:\n    enabled: true\n    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n  backend:\n    enabled: true\n    stack_hint: \"Build from scratch - no existing RBAC (per interview Q2=D)\"\n  mobile:\n    enabled: false\n    stack_hint: \"\"\n\nuser_flows:\n  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n      - \"Frontend updates auth state without refresh\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"Insufficient admin permissions → 403 with audit log\"\n      - \"WebSocket unavailable → graceful degradation\"\n  - id: \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    actors: [\"user\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"POST/PUT/DELETE APIs\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"User attempts restricted action\"\n      - \"RBAC middleware checks JWT claims\"\n      - \"Access denied → 403 Forbidden\"\n      - \"Attempt logged to audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\"\n      - \"Frontend displays permission error\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"JWT token expired → 401 (not 403)\"\n  - id: \"flow.live-session-update\"\n    actors: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"WebSocket connection\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"User active in React app\"\n      - \"Admin revokes role via API\"\n      - \"WebSocket server broadcasts update\"\n      - \"Redux store updates auth state\"\n      - \"UI immediately hides restricted elements\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"Connection lost → exponential backoff reconnect\"\n\nui_ux:\n  screens:\n    - \"Admin role management interface (existing)\"\n    - \"Permission denied error display\"\n  states:\n    loading: [\"WebSocket connection status indicator\"]\n    empty: []\n    error: [\"403 permission denied message\", \"WebSocket connection error\"]\n    partial_success: []\n  accessibility:\n    - \"Error messages must be screen-reader accessible\"\n  i18n:\n    - \"Permission error messages need i18n support\"\n  analytics_events:\n    - \"role_change_denied\"\n    - \"permission_check_failed\"\n\napi_contract:\n  - id: \"ALL POST/PUT/DELETE /*\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"application/json\"\n      body_schema: {}\n    response:\n      success_schema: {}\n      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"401 Unauthorized\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 5000\n  - id: \"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer (admin only)\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"application/json\"\n      body_schema:\n        role: \"string\"\n    response:\n      success_schema:\n        user_id: \"string\"\n        new_role: \"string\"\n        updated_at: \"timestamp\"\n      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"404 Not Found\", \"400 Bad Request\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 3000\n  - id: \"WS /ws/session\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer (upgrade)\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"N/A\"\n      body_schema: {}\n    response:\n      success_schema:\n        event: \"role_updated\"\n        payload:\n          user_id: \"string\"\n          new_role: \"string\"\n          timestamp: \"string\"\n      error_codes: [\"401 Unauthorized\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 30000\n\ndata_model:\n  entities:\n    - name: \"audit_log\"\n      fields:\n        - \"id: UUID PK\"\n        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n        - \"action: ENUM(GRANT, REVOKE, DENIED)\"\n        - \"target_resource: STRING\"\n        - \"role_changes: JSONB\"\n        - \"timestamp: TIMESTAMP\"\n        - \"ip_address: INET\"\n        - \"user_agent: STRING\"\n    - name: \"user_sessions\"\n      fields:\n        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n        - \"role: STRING\"\n        - \"permissions: JSONB\"\n        - \"last_updated: TIMESTAMP\"\n  schema_changes:\n    required: true\n    notes: \"New audit_log table required; user_sessions cache table optional for performance\"\n  versioning: \"backward\"\n  idempotency: \"Role updates must be idempotent (same role set = no-op)\"\n\ntradeoffs:\n  - topic: \"RBAC check caching strategy\"\n    options:\n      - name: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n        pros: [\"Fast (<10ms)\", \"Simple implementation\"]\n        cons: [\"Stale data risk\", \"Per-node cache\"]\n      - name: \"Redis distributed cache\"\n        pros: [\"Consistent across nodes\", \"Configurable TTL\"]\n        cons: [\"Network latency\", \"Additional infrastructure\"]\n    decision: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n    rationale: \"Meet P95 <10ms latency requirement; accept eventual consistency for role changes via WebSocket push\"\n  - topic: \"Session sync mechanism\"\n    options:\n      - name: \"WebSocket push\"\n        pros: [\"Real-time updates\", \"Efficient\"]\n        cons: [\"Connection management complexity\"]\n      - name: \"Short polling\"\n        pros: [\"Simple implementation\", \"No persistent connections\"]\n        cons: [\"Higher latency\", \"Unnecessary load\"]\n    decision: \"WebSocket push\"\n    rationale: \"<5 second sync requirement demands WebSocket; polling would add unnecessary load\"\n\nrisks:\n  - risk: \"Performance impact from live RBAC checks on every request\"\n    impact: \"high\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"In-memory caching with TTL\"\n      - \"Async audit logging\"\n    detection:\n      - \"RBAC latency P95 metrics\"\n      - \"Alert if >10ms\"\n  - risk: \"Session desync between backend and frontend\"\n    impact: \"med\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"WebSocket with heartbeat\"\n      - \"Fallback to polling\"\n    detection:\n      - \"WebSocket connection metrics\"\n      - \"Role mismatch logs\"\n  - risk: \"Audit log storage growth\"\n    impact: \"med\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"Retention policy (90 days)\"\n      - \"Archive to cold storage\"\n    detection:\n      - \"Storage usage monitoring\"\n      - \"Growth rate alerts\"\n  - risk: \"WebSocket connection instability\"\n    impact: \"high\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"Graceful degradation\"\n      - \"Exponential backoff reconnect\"\n    detection:\n      - \"Connection uptime metrics\"\n      - \"Error rate monitoring\"\n\nobservability:\n  logs:\n    - \"RBAC check results (allowed/denied)\"\n    - \"Audit log writes\"\n    - \"WebSocket connection events\"\n  metrics:\n    - \"rbac_check_latency_p95\"\n    - \"rbac_check_denied_total\"\n    - \"audit_log_writes_total\"\n    - \"websocket_connections_active\"\n    - \"websocket_events_sent_total\"\n  traces:\n    - \"RBAC decision path\"\n    - \"WebSocket message flow\"\n  dashboards:\n    - \"RBAC Performance Dashboard\"\n    - \"Audit Log Activity\"\n\nroll_out:\n  feature_flags:\n    - name: \"rbac_live_enforcement\"\n      description: \"Enable live RBAC checks on mutation APIs\"\n    - name: \"websocket_session_sync\"\n      description: \"Enable WebSocket session updates\"\n  stages:\n    - \"Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\"\n    - \"Phase 2: WebSocket infrastructure\"\n    - \"Phase 3: Frontend integration\"\n    - \"Phase 4: E2E testing + performance validation\"\n  rollback:\n    - \"Disable feature flags\"\n    - \"Revert to previous middleware version\"\n\ntest_strategy:\n  unit:\n    scope:\n      - \"RBAC middleware logic\"\n      - \"JWT claims parsing\"\n      - \"Audit log formatting\"\n  integration:\n    scope:\n      - \"RBAC middleware + JWT integration\"\n      - \"Audit log database writes\"\n      - \"WebSocket connection handling\"\n  contract:\n    scope:\n      - \"API response schemas\"\n      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n  e2e:\n    scope:\n      - \"Admin role change flow\"\n      - \"Permission denied flow\"\n      - \"Live session update flow\"\n    critical_paths:\n      - \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n      - \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n      - \"flow.live-session-update\"\n  test_data:\n    fixtures:\n      - \"Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions\"\n      - \"Regular user with limited role\"\n      - \"User with expired JWT\"\n  environments:\n    stage:\n      - \"Integration test environment\"\n      - \"Load test environment\"\n\nopen_questions:\n  blocker: []\n  non_blocker:\n    - \"What is the preferred audit log retention period beyond 90 days?\"\n    - \"Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\"\n\ndone_definition:\n  acceptance_criteria_map:\n    - ac: \"AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users\"\n      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    - ac: \"AC-2: All role operations logged to audit_log\"\n      test_coverage: \"integration audit_log writes\"\n    - ac: \"AC-3: Frontend updates within 5 seconds of backend change\"\n      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.live-session-update\"\n    - ac: \"AC-4: RBAC latency P95 <= 10ms at 1000 RPS\"\n      test_coverage: \"load test validation\"\n  manual_checks:\n    - \"Verify WebSocket graceful degradation when connection lost\"\n    - \"Verify audit logs do not contain sensitive data\"\n","numLines":329,"startLine":1,"totalLines":329}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_bcMNrAWgbUkUbitPrnpTWO8g","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→**Status:** READY\n     4→**Ticket:** TST-001\n     5→**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n     6→**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## Executive Summary\n    11→\n    12→This plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n    13→\n    14→| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n    15→|----------------|------------------|------------|\n    16→| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n    17→| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n    18→| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n    19→| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n    20→\n    21→---\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    24→\n    25→### Architecture Decisions\n    26→\n    27→1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n    28→\n    29→2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n    30→\n    31→3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n    32→\n    33→4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n    34→\n    35→5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    40→\n    41→- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n    42→- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n    43→- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n    44→- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n    45→- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## AIDD:RISKS\n    50→\n    51→| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n    52→|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n    53→| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n    54→| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n    55→| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n    56→| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n    57→| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n    58→| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n    59→| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n    60→| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n    61→\n    62→### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n    63→\n    64→**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\n    65→The application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n    66→- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n    67→\n    68→**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\n    69→The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n    70→- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table\n    71→\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→## Milestones & Iterations\n    75→\n    76→### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n    77→**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n    78→\n    79→#### 1.1 Database Migration\n    80→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n    81→\n    82→```yaml\n    83→# Create audit_log table\n    84→- changeSet:\n    85→    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    86→    author: ai-advent\n    87→    context: rbac\n    88→    changes:\n    89→      - createTable:\n    90→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n    91→          columns:\n    92→            - column:\n    93→                name: id\n    94→                type: UUID\n    95→                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n    96→                constraints:\n    97→                  primaryKey: true\n    98→            - column:\n    99→                name: timestamp\n   100→                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n   101→                defaultValueComputed: now()\n   102→                constraints:\n   103→                  nullable: false\n   104→            - column:\n   105→                name: actor_namespace\n   106→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   107→                constraints:\n   108→                  nullable: false\n   109→            - column:\n   110→                name: actor_reference\n   111→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   112→                constraints:\n   113→                  nullable: false\n   114→            - column:\n   115→                name: action\n   116→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   117→                constraints:\n   118→                  nullable: false\n   119→            - column:\n   120→                name: target_resource\n   121→                type: VARCHAR(256)\n   122→            - column:\n   123→                name: target_profile_namespace\n   124→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   125→            - column:\n   126→                name: target_profile_reference\n   127→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   128→            - column:\n   129→                name: result\n   130→                type: VARCHAR(16)\n   131→                constraints:\n   132→                  nullable: false\n   133→            - column:\n   134→                name: http_method\n   135→                type: VARCHAR(8)\n   136→            - column:\n   137→                name: http_path\n   138→                type: VARCHAR(512)\n   139→            - column:\n   140→                name: metadata\n   141→                type: JSONB\n   142→      - createIndex:\n   143→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   144→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n   145→          columns:\n   146→            - column:\n   147→                name: timestamp\n   148→      - createIndex:\n   149→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   150→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n   151→          columns:\n   152→            - column:\n   153→                name: actor_namespace\n   154→            - column:\n   155→                name: actor_reference\n   156→```\n   157→\n   158→#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n   159→**Files to create:**\n   160→\n   161→| File | Purpose |\n   162→|------|---------|\n   163→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n   164→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n   165→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n   166→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n   167→\n   168→#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n   169→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n   170→\n   171→```java\n   172→@Component\n   173→@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\n   174→public class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n   175→\n   176→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   177→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   178→    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n   179→\n   180→    @Override\n   181→    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n   182→        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n   183→        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n   184→\n   185→        // Skip non-mutation methods\n   186→        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n   187→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   188→        }\n   189→\n   190→        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n   191→        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n   192→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   193→        }\n   194→\n   195→        // Extract identity from headers\n   196→        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n   197→        if (identity == null) {\n   198→            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n   199→        }\n   200→\n   201→        // Check required roles for path\n   202→        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n   203→\n   204→        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n   205→            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n   206→                if (hasRole) {\n   207→                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n   208→                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n   209→                } else {\n   210→                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n   211→                }\n   212→            })\n   213→            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n   214→                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n   215→                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n   216→            });\n   217→    }\n   218→\n   219→    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n   220→                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   221→        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n   222→        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n   223→        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n   224→        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n   225→        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n   226→        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n   227→    }\n   228→}\n   229→```\n   230→\n   231→#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n   232→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n   233→\n   234→```java\n   235→@Service\n   236→public class ProfileRoleService {\n   237→\n   238→    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n   239→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   240→\n   241→    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n   242→                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n   243→        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n   244→        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n   245→            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n   246→            .maximumSize(10_000)\n   247→            .recordStats()\n   248→            .build(this::loadRoles);\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   252→        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n   256→        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n   257→            return Mono.just(true);\n   258→        }\n   259→        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n   260→            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n   261→            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   265→        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n   266→    }\n   267→\n   268→    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n   269→        return roleCache.stats();\n   270→    }\n   271→}\n   272→```\n   273→\n   274→#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n   275→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n   276→\n   277→```java\n   278→@Service\n   279→public class AuditLogService {\n   280→\n   281→    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n   282→    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n   283→\n   284→    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n   285→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   286→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   287→            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   288→            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   289→            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n   290→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   291→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   292→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   293→            entry.setResult(result);\n   294→            repository.save(entry);\n   295→        });\n   296→    }\n   297→\n   298→    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   299→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   300→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   301→            if (identity != null) {\n   302→                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   303→                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   304→            }\n   305→            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n   306→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   307→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   308→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   309→            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n   310→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n   311→            repository.save(entry);\n   312→        });\n   313→    }\n   314→\n   315→    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n   316→                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n   317→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   318→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   319→            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n   320→            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n   321→            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n   322→            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n   323→            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n   324→            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n   325→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n   326→            repository.save(entry);\n   327→        });\n   328→    }\n   329→\n   330→    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n   331→        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n   332→            try {\n   333→                task.run();\n   334→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   335→                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n   336→            }\n   337→        });\n   338→    }\n   339→}\n   340→```\n   341→\n   342→#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n   343→**Files:**\n   344→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n   345→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n   346→\n   347→---\n   348→\n   349→### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n   350→**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n   351→\n   352→#### 2.1 Profile Client\n   353→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n   354→\n   355→```java\n   356→@Component\n   357→public class ProfileClient {\n   358→\n   359→    private final WebClient webClient;\n   360→    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n   361→\n   362→    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n   363→                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n   364→        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n   365→        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n   366→    }\n   367→\n   368→    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   369→        try {\n   370→            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n   371→                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n   372→                .retrieve()\n   373→                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n   374→                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n   375→                .block();\n   376→\n   377→            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n   378→                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n   379→                : Set.of();\n   380→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   381→            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n   382→            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n   383→            return Set.of();\n   384→        }\n   385→    }\n   386→}\n   387→```\n   388→\n   389→#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n   390→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n   391→\n   392→```java\n   393→public record ProfileResponse(\n   394→    String profileId,\n   395→    String namespace,\n   396→    String reference,\n   397→    List<String> roles,\n   398→    Instant updatedAt\n   399→) {}\n   400→```\n   401→\n   402→#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n   403→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n   404→\n   405→```java\n   406→@Configuration\n   407→@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\n   408→public class RbacConfiguration {\n   409→\n   410→    @Bean\n   411→    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n   412→        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n   413→    }\n   414→}\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n   418→\n   419→```java\n   420→@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\n   421→public record RbacProperties(\n   422→    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n   423→    List<String> publicPaths,\n   424→    int cacheTtlMinutes\n   425→) {\n   426→    public record PathRule(\n   427→        String path,\n   428→        Set<String> methods,\n   429→        Set<String> requiredRoles\n   430→    ) {}\n   431→}\n   432→```\n   433→\n   434→---\n   435→\n   436→### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n   437→**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n   438→\n   439→#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n   440→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n   441→\n   442→```typescript\n   443→// Add to ProfileStoreState\n   444→type ProfileStoreState = {\n   445→  // ... existing fields\n   446→  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n   447→  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n   448→  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n   449→};\n   450→\n   451→// Add to store implementation\n   452→export const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n   453→  persist(\n   454→    (set, get) => ({\n   455→      // ... existing initial state\n   456→      roleVersion: 0,\n   457→      lastRoleSync: null,\n   458→\n   459→      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n   460→        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n   461→        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n   462→\n   463→        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n   464→        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n   465→        params.set('reference', reference);\n   466→        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n   467→        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n   468→\n   469→        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n   470→          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n   471→        );\n   472→\n   473→        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n   474→          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n   475→          set((state) => ({\n   476→            profile: state.profile ? {\n   477→              ...state.profile,\n   478→              roles: data.roles,\n   479→              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n   480→            } : null,\n   481→            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n   482→            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n   483→          }));\n   484→        });\n   485→\n   486→        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n   487→          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n   488→          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n   489→        };\n   490→\n   491→        return () => eventSource.close();\n   492→      },\n   493→    }),\n   494→    // ... existing persist config\n   495→  ),\n   496→);\n   497→```\n   498→\n   499→#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n   500→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n   501→\n   502→```typescript\n   503→import { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\n   504→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   505→\n   506→export function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n   507→  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n   508→  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n   509→\n   510→  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n   511→  useEffect(() => {\n   512→    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n   513→    return unsubscribe;\n   514→  }, []);\n   515→\n   516→  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n   517→    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n   518→    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n   519→  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n   520→\n   521→  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n   522→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n   523→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   524→\n   525→  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n   526→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n   527→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   528→\n   529→  return {\n   530→    roles,\n   531→    hasRole,\n   532→    hasAnyRole,\n   533→    hasAllRoles,\n   534→    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n   535→    roleVersion,\n   536→  };\n   537→}\n   538→```\n   539→\n   540→#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n   541→**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n   542→\n   543→Replace inline role check with hook:\n   544→\n   545→```typescript\n   546→// Replace lines 34-36:\n   547→const { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n   548→\n   549→// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n   550→```\n   551→\n   552→#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n   553→**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n   554→\n   555→```typescript\n   556→import React from 'react';\n   557→import { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n   558→\n   559→interface RoleGuardProps {\n   560→  requiredRole: string;\n   561→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   562→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   563→}\n   564→\n   565→export const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n   566→  requiredRole,\n   567→  fallback = null,\n   568→  children,\n   569→}) => {\n   570→  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n   571→  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n   572→};\n   573→\n   574→interface AdminGuardProps {\n   575→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   576→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   577→}\n   578→\n   579→export const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n   580→  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n   581→    {children}\n   582→  </RoleGuard>\n   583→);\n   584→```\n   585→\n   586→---\n   587→\n   588→### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n   589→**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n   590→\n   591→#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n   592→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n   593→\n   594→```java\n   595→@Service\n   596→public class RoleEventService {\n   597→\n   598→    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n   599→\n   600→    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   601→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n   602→        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n   603→\n   604→        return sink.asFlux()\n   605→            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n   606→            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n   607→    }\n   608→\n   609→    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n   610→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n   611→        if (sink != null) {\n   612→            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n   613→        }\n   614→    }\n   615→\n   616→    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n   617→        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n   618→    }\n   619→\n   620→    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n   621→}\n   622→```\n   623→\n   624→#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n   625→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n   626→\n   627→```java\n   628→@RestController\n   629→@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\n   630→public class RoleEventsController {\n   631→\n   632→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   633→\n   634→    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n   635→    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n   636→            @RequestParam String namespace,\n   637→            @RequestParam String reference,\n   638→            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n   639→            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n   640→\n   641→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n   642→\n   643→        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n   644→            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n   645→                .event(\"role-change\")\n   646→                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n   647→                .build())\n   648→            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n   649→    }\n   650→\n   651→    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n   652→        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n   653→            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n   654→                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n   655→                .build());\n   656→    }\n   657→}\n   658→```\n   659→\n   660→#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n   661→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n   662→\n   663→```java\n   664→@Service\n   665→public class RoleAssignmentService {\n   666→\n   667→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   668→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   669→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   670→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   671→\n   672→    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   673→        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n   674→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   675→                // Invalidate cache\n   676→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   677→                // Notify user\n   678→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   679→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   680→                // Audit\n   681→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n   682→            });\n   683→    }\n   684→\n   685→    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   686→        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n   687→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   688→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   689→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   690→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   691→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n   692→            });\n   693→    }\n   694→}\n   695→```\n   696→\n   697→---\n   698→\n   699→### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n   700→**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n   701→\n   702→#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n   703→\n   704→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n   705→\n   706→```java\n   707→@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\n   708→class RbacWebFilterTest {\n   709→\n   710→    @MockBean\n   711→    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   712→\n   713→    @MockBean\n   714→    private AuditLogService auditService;\n   715→\n   716→    @Autowired\n   717→    private WebTestClient webClient;\n   718→\n   719→    @Test\n   720→    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n   721→        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   722→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   723→            .exchange()\n   724→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   725→    }\n   726→\n   727→    @Test\n   728→    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n   729→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n   730→\n   731→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   732→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   733→            .exchange()\n   734→            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n   735→\n   736→        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n   737→    }\n   738→\n   739→    @Test\n   740→    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n   741→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n   742→\n   743→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   744→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n   745→            .exchange()\n   746→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   747→    }\n   748→}\n   749→```\n   750→\n   751→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n   752→\n   753→```java\n   754→class ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n   755→\n   756→    @Test\n   757→    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n   758→        // First call hits profile service\n   759→        // Second call uses cache\n   760→        // Verify cache stats\n   761→    }\n   762→\n   763→    @Test\n   764→    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n   765→        // When profile service unavailable\n   766→        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n   767→    }\n   768→}\n   769→```\n   770→\n   771→#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n   772→\n   773→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n   774→\n   775→```typescript\n   776→import { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\n   777→import { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\n   778→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   779→\n   780→describe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n   781→  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n   782→    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n   783→\n   784→    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n   785→\n   786→    // Simulate role change event\n   787→    useProfileStore.setState({\n   788→      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n   789→      roleVersion: 1,\n   790→    });\n   791→\n   792→    await waitFor(() => {\n   793→      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n   794→    });\n   795→  });\n   796→});\n   797→```\n   798→\n   799→#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n   800→\n   801→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n   802→\n   803→```java\n   804→@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\n   805→class RbacIntegrationTest {\n   806→\n   807→    @Test\n   808→    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n   809→        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n   810→        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n   811→        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n   812→        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n   813→        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n   814→    }\n   815→}\n   816→```\n   817→\n   818→#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n   819→\n   820→```java\n   821→@Test\n   822→void rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n   823→    // Run 1000 requests\n   824→    // Measure RBAC check time\n   825→    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n   826→}\n   827→```\n   828→\n   829→---\n   830→\n   831→## Files to Create/Modify\n   832→\n   833→### New Files (Backend)\n   834→\n   835→| Path | Purpose |\n   836→|------|---------|\n   837→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n   838→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n   839→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n   840→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n   841→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n   842→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n   843→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n   844→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n   845→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n   846→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n   847→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n   848→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n   849→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n   850→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n   851→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n   852→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n   853→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n   854→| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n   855→\n   856→### Modified Files (Backend)\n   857→\n   858→| Path | Changes |\n   859→|------|---------|\n   860→| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n   861→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n   862→\n   863→### New Files (Frontend)\n   864→\n   865→| Path | Purpose |\n   866→|------|---------|\n   867→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n   868→| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n   869→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n   870→\n   871→### Modified Files (Frontend)\n   872→\n   873→| Path | Changes |\n   874→|------|---------|\n   875→| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n   876→| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n   877→| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n   878→\n   879→---\n   880→\n   881→## Configuration\n   882→\n   883→### application-rbac.yaml\n   884→\n   885→```yaml\n   886→rbac:\n   887→  cache:\n   888→    ttl-minutes: 5\n   889→  protected-paths:\n   890→    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n   891→      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n   892→      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n   893→    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n   894→      methods: [\"*\"]\n   895→      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n   896→  public-paths:\n   897→    - \"/actuator/health\"\n   898→    - \"/api/public/**\"\n   899→    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n   900→\n   901→profile:\n   902→  service:\n   903→    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n   904→```\n   905→\n   906→---\n   907→\n   908→## Rollout Plan\n   909→\n   910→### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n   911→1. Run database migration\n   912→2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n   913→3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n   914→\n   915→### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n   916→1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n   917→2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n   918→3. Verify cache hit rates\n   919→\n   920→### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n   921→1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n   922→2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n   923→3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n   924→\n   925→### Rollback Plan\n   926→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n   927→- Quick disable via config change\n   928→- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n   929→\n   930→---\n   931→\n   932→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n   933→\n   934→- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n   935→- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n   936→- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n   937→- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n   938→- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n   939→\n   940→---\n   941→\n   942→## AIDD:METRICS\n   943→\n   944→| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n   945→|--------|--------|-------------|\n   946→| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n   947→| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n   948→| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n   949→| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n   950→| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n   951→\n   952→---\n   953→\n   954→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n   955→\n   956→None — all questions resolved via research findings.\n   957→\n   958→---\n   959→\n   960→## AIDD:READ_LOG\n   961→\n   962→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n   963→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n   964→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n   965→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n   966→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n   967→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n   968→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n   969→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n   970→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n   971→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n   972→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n   973→\n   974→---\n   975→\n   976→## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n   977→\n   978→- Created plan document with 5 phases\n   979→- Defined 19 new backend files\n   980→- Defined 3 new frontend files\n   981→- Specified 4 modified files\n   982→- Created database migration schema\n   983→- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n   984→- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n   985→\n   986→---\n   987→\n   988→## AIDD:VALIDATION_FEEDBACK\n   989→\n   990→**Validation Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n   991→**Validation Report:** `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n   992→\n   993→### Validation Findings Addressed\n   994→\n   995→| Finding | Status | Resolution |\n   996→|---------|--------|------------|\n   997→| Component scan configuration | Documented | Add RbacConfig to all profile configs |\n   998→| Profile service integration | Documented | Define contract or implement local role storage |\n   999→| RbacPathMatcher implementation | Documented | Complete in Phase 1.6 |\n  1000→| Feature flags for rollout | Recommended | Add to application-rbac.yaml |\n  1001→\n  1002→### Critical Items for Implementation\n  1003→\n  1004→1. **R-008 (High Risk)**: Verify profile service API exists or implement `rbac_profile_roles` table\n  1005→2. **R-007 (Medium Risk)**: Add RBAC configuration to `McpApplication.java` profile imports\n  1006→3. **Path Matcher**: Complete `RbacPathMatcher` implementation with explicit path rules\n  1007→\n  1008→---\n  1009→\n  1010→**Status:** READY for implementation (with validation WARN items noted)\n  1011→**Next Action:** Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n  1012→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"6f07ef6e-3ac3-446c-b2e8-3fc2272ce2ae","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md","content":"# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n**Status:** READY\n**Ticket:** TST-001\n**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n\n| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n|----------------|------------------|------------|\n| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n\n### Architecture Decisions\n\n1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n\n2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n\n3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n\n4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n\n5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n\n- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n\n### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n\n**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\nThe application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n\n**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\nThe plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table\n\n---\n\n## Milestones & Iterations\n\n### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n\n#### 1.1 Database Migration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n# Create audit_log table\n- changeSet:\n    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    author: ai-advent\n    context: rbac\n    changes:\n      - createTable:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: id\n                type: UUID\n                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n                constraints:\n                  primaryKey: true\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n                defaultValueComputed: now()\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: action\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: target_resource\n                type: VARCHAR(256)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n            - column:\n                name: result\n                type: VARCHAR(16)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: http_method\n                type: VARCHAR(8)\n            - column:\n                name: http_path\n                type: VARCHAR(512)\n            - column:\n                name: metadata\n                type: JSONB\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n```\n\n#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n**Files to create:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n\n#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\n@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\npublic class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n\n    @Override\n    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n\n        // Skip non-mutation methods\n        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Extract identity from headers\n        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n        if (identity == null) {\n            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n        }\n\n        // Check required roles for path\n        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n\n        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n                if (hasRole) {\n                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n                } else {\n                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n                }\n            })\n            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n            });\n    }\n\n    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class ProfileRoleService {\n\n    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n\n    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n            .maximumSize(10_000)\n            .recordStats()\n            .build(this::loadRoles);\n    }\n\n    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n            return Mono.just(true);\n        }\n        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n    }\n\n    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n    }\n\n    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n        return roleCache.stats();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class AuditLogService {\n\n    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n\n    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(result);\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            if (identity != null) {\n                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            }\n            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n            try {\n                task.run();\n            } catch (Exception e) {\n                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n**Files:**\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n\n#### 2.1 Profile Client\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class ProfileClient {\n\n    private final WebClient webClient;\n    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n\n    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n    }\n\n    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        try {\n            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n                .retrieve()\n                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n                .block();\n\n            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n                : Set.of();\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n            return Set.of();\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n\n```java\npublic record ProfileResponse(\n    String profileId,\n    String namespace,\n    String reference,\n    List<String> roles,\n    Instant updatedAt\n) {}\n```\n\n#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n\n```java\n@Configuration\n@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\npublic class RbacConfiguration {\n\n    @Bean\n    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n\n```java\n@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\npublic record RbacProperties(\n    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n    List<String> publicPaths,\n    int cacheTtlMinutes\n) {\n    public record PathRule(\n        String path,\n        Set<String> methods,\n        Set<String> requiredRoles\n    ) {}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n\n#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n\n```typescript\n// Add to ProfileStoreState\ntype ProfileStoreState = {\n  // ... existing fields\n  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n};\n\n// Add to store implementation\nexport const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n  persist(\n    (set, get) => ({\n      // ... existing initial state\n      roleVersion: 0,\n      lastRoleSync: null,\n\n      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n\n        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n        params.set('reference', reference);\n        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n\n        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n        );\n\n        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n          set((state) => ({\n            profile: state.profile ? {\n              ...state.profile,\n              roles: data.roles,\n              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n            } : null,\n            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n          }));\n        });\n\n        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n        };\n\n        return () => eventSource.close();\n      },\n    }),\n    // ... existing persist config\n  ),\n);\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\nexport function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n\n  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n    return unsubscribe;\n  }, []);\n\n  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  return {\n    roles,\n    hasRole,\n    hasAnyRole,\n    hasAllRoles,\n    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n    roleVersion,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n\nReplace inline role check with hook:\n\n```typescript\n// Replace lines 34-36:\nconst { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n\n// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n```\n\n#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport React from 'react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n\ninterface RoleGuardProps {\n  requiredRole: string;\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n  requiredRole,\n  fallback = null,\n  children,\n}) => {\n  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n};\n\ninterface AdminGuardProps {\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n    {children}\n  </RoleGuard>\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n\n#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleEventService {\n\n    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n\n    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n\n        return sink.asFlux()\n            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n    }\n\n    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n        if (sink != null) {\n            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n    }\n\n    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\npublic class RoleEventsController {\n\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n\n    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n            @RequestParam String namespace,\n            @RequestParam String reference,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n\n        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n\n        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n                .event(\"role-change\")\n                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n                .build())\n            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n    }\n\n    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n                .build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleAssignmentService {\n\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                // Invalidate cache\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                // Notify user\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                // Audit\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n\n#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n\n```java\n@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\nclass RbacWebFilterTest {\n\n    @MockBean\n    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    @MockBean\n    private AuditLogService auditService;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private WebTestClient webClient;\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n\n        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n\n```java\nclass ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n        // First call hits profile service\n        // Second call uses cache\n        // Verify cache stats\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n        // When profile service unavailable\n        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\ndescribe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n\n    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n\n    // Simulate role change event\n    useProfileStore.setState({\n      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n      roleVersion: 1,\n    });\n\n    await waitFor(() => {\n      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n\n```java\n@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\nclass RbacIntegrationTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n\n```java\n@Test\nvoid rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n    // Run 1000 requests\n    // Measure RBAC check time\n    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### New Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n\n### Modified Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n\n### New Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n\n### Modified Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### application-rbac.yaml\n\n```yaml\nrbac:\n  cache:\n    ttl-minutes: 5\n  protected-paths:\n    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n      methods: [\"*\"]\n      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n  public-paths:\n    - \"/actuator/health\"\n    - \"/api/public/**\"\n    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n\nprofile:\n  service:\n    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollout Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n1. Run database migration\n2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n\n### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n3. Verify cache hit rates\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n\n### Rollback Plan\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n- Quick disable via config change\n- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n\n- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:METRICS\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n\nNone — all questions resolved via research findings.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:READ_LOG\n\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n\n- Created plan document with 5 phases\n- Defined 19 new backend files\n- Defined 3 new frontend files\n- Specified 4 modified files\n- Created database migration schema\n- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:VALIDATION_FEEDBACK\n\n**Validation Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n**Validation Report:** `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n\n### Validation Findings Addressed\n\n| Finding | Status | Resolution |\n|---------|--------|------------|\n| Component scan configuration | Documented | Add RbacConfig to all profile configs |\n| Profile service integration | Documented | Define contract or implement local role storage |\n| RbacPathMatcher implementation | Documented | Complete in Phase 1.6 |\n| Feature flags for rollout | Recommended | Add to application-rbac.yaml |\n\n### Critical Items for Implementation\n\n1. **R-008 (High Risk)**: Verify profile service API exists or implement `rbac_profile_roles` table\n2. **R-007 (Medium Risk)**: Add RBAC configuration to `McpApplication.java` profile imports\n3. **Path Matcher**: Complete `RbacPathMatcher` implementation with explicit path rules\n\n---\n\n**Status:** READY for implementation (with validation WARN items noted)\n**Next Action:** Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n","numLines":1012,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1012}}}
