response schemas\"\n   290→      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n   291→  e2e:\n   292→    scope:\n   293→      - \"Admin role change flow\"\n   294→      - \"Permission denied flow\"\n   295→      - \"Live session update flow\"\n   296→    critical_paths:\n   297→      - \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n   298→      - \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   299→      - \"flow.live-session-update\"\n   300→  test_data:\n   301→    fixtures:\n   302→      - \"Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions\"\n   303→      - \"Regular user with limited role\"\n   304→      - \"User with expired JWT\"\n   305→  environments:\n   306→    stage:\n   307→      - \"Integration test environment\"\n   308→      - \"Load test environment\"\n   309→\n   310→open_questions:\n   311→  blocker: []\n   312→  non_blocker:\n   313→    - \"What is the preferred audit log retention period beyond 90 days?\"\n   314→    - \"Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\"\n   315→\n   316→done_definition:\n   317→  acceptance_criteria_map:\n   318→    - ac: \"AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users\"\n   319→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   320→    - ac: \"AC-2: All role operations logged to audit_log\"\n   321→      test_coverage: \"integration audit_log writes\"\n   322→    - ac: \"AC-3: Frontend updates within 5 seconds of backend change\"\n   323→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.live-session-update\"\n   324→    - ac: \"AC-4: RBAC latency P95 <= 10ms at 1000 RPS\"\n   325→      test_coverage: \"load test validation\"\n   326→  manual_checks:\n   327→    - \"Verify WebSocket graceful degradation when connection lost\"\n   328→    - \"Verify audit logs do not contain sensitive data\"\n   329→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing co