er/<ticket>/TST-001.json msg=blocked`\n   302→- YYYY-MM-DD source=implement id=I1 kind=iteration hash=abc123 link=aidd/reports/tests/<ticket>/TST-001.jsonl msg=...\n   303→\n   304→---\n   305→\n   306→## AIDD:HOW_TO_UPDATE\n   307→- Правило итерации: **1 чекбокс** (или 2 тесно связанных) — затем Stop.\n   308→- Отмечайте чекбоксы так:\n   309→  - `- [x] I1: <title> (iteration_id: I1) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n   310→  - `- [x] <handoff title> (id: review:F6) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n   311→- После каждого [x] обновляй `AIDD:NEXT_3` (pointer list) и добавляй запись в `AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG`.\n   312→- Если меняешь тестовый профиль/команды — обнови `AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`.\n   313→- Если обновили spec — запусти `/feature-dev-aidd:tasks-new` для синхронизации tasklist.\n   314→- Логи/stacktrace не вставлять в tasklist — только ссылки на `aidd/reports/**`.\n   315→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_SPCVf4ry7GW8G9G1zonJulEx","session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"3563cd9e-1fb0-427b-b6a9-8b86182e857b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_xvkn8gxy05Yz6D1smqzMXwQl","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"tool_TFPg7nq1zEbGE9tyzTqlxVTr","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md","content":"---\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\nStatus: READY\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nOwner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\nPRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\nPlan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\nResearch: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\nReports:\n  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n---\n\n# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nStage: tasklist\nStatus: READY\n\n### TL;DR\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n\n### Scope & boundaries\n- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n- Integrations / dependencies:\n  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n\n### Decisions & defaults (living)\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n\n### Test policy (iteration budget)\n- Cadence: checkpoint\n- Profile: targeted\n- Tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`, `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Filters: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Budget minutes: 10\n- Known flaky / failing: none\n\n### Commands quickstart (copy/paste)\n- Format: cmd\n- Tests (manual): `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*Rbac*\"`, `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Run/Dev: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:bootRun`, `npm run dev` (frontend)\n- DB migration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n\n### Open questions / blockers\n- None — all questions resolved via PRD decisions Q1-Q5\n\n### Blockers summary (handoff)\n- None\n\n### References\n- Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (OUTDATED — uses WebSocket, follow Plan for SSE)\n- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md (Status: READY, Q5=B polling but Plan uses SSE)\n- Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n- Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md (Status: READY, source of truth for implementation)\n- Reports:\n  - review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  - reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  - qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:SPEC_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (status: draft — OUTDATED)\n\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement on mutation APIs with auditable role operations and SSE-based frontend synchronization\n- Non-goals:\n  - UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n  - Migration of historical access logs\n  - Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n  - WebSocket (Spec says WebSocket, but Plan uses SSE — follow Plan)\n- Key decisions:\n  - Backend: Custom WebFlux filter for RBAC (no Spring Security)\n  - Auth: X-Profile-Key header-based identity extraction\n  - Frontend: React + Zustand (not Redux as in Spec)\n  - Session Sync: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — NOT WebSocket, NOT Polling\n  - Cache: Caffeine with 5min TTL\n  - Audit: PostgreSQL table `rbac_audit_log` with JSONB metadata\n- Risks:\n  - R-001: Profile service unavailable → Circuit breaker, fail-closed, cache roles\n  - R-002: Cache stale roles after assignment → Cache invalidation on role change\n  - R-003: SSE connection memory leak → Proper cleanup on disconnect\n  - R-004: Audit log write failures → Async logging, error queue\n  - R-005: RBAC filter performance degradation → Caffeine cache, async audit\n  - R-006: Breaking change to existing APIs → Feature flags, audit-only mode first\n  - R-007: Component scan misses RBAC beans → Add to all profile configs\n  - R-008: Missing profile service integration → Define contract or implement local role storage\n\n## AIDD:TEST_STRATEGY\n- Unit:\n  - Scope: RBAC middleware logic, role caching, audit log formatting, useRoleGuard hook\n  - Files: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Integration:\n  - Scope: RBAC filter + profile service client, audit log DB writes, SSE endpoint connection handling\n  - Files: `RbacIntegrationTest`, `RoleEventsControllerTest`\n- Contract:\n  - Scope: API response schemas (403 format), SSE event format\n  - Files: Contract tests for `/api/profiles/role-events` endpoint\n- E2E/Stand:\n  - Critical paths:\n    - flow.admin-change-role: Admin assigns role → user receives SSE update\n    - flow.unauthorized-access: User attempts restricted action → 403 + audit log\n    - flow.live-session-update: Role change propagates to frontend within 5 seconds\n- Test data:\n  - Fixtures: Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions, regular user with limited role, user with missing headers\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION\n> Конкретные команды/фильтры запуска (execution‑уровень).\n- profile: targeted\n- tasks:\n  - Backend: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n  - Frontend: `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n  - Integration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacIntegrationTest*\"`\n- filters:\n  - `RbacWebFilterTest` — filter logic tests\n  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest` — caching and role resolution tests\n  - `AuditLogServiceTest` — audit logging tests\n  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts` — frontend hook tests\n- when: checkpoint\n- reason: Fast feedback on RBAC module changes; full suite on PR\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL\n\n### I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model (iteration_id: I1)\n- parent_iteration_id: none\n- Goal: Create database schema for audit logging and establish RBAC domain model\n- Outputs:\n  - `db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` — migration for rbac_audit_log table\n  - `Role.java` — Role enum (ADMIN, USER, VIEWER)\n  - `ProfileIdentity.java` — Value object for namespace:reference\n  - `Permission.java` — Permission enum (READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN)\n  - `RbacDecision.java` — Decision record\n  - `AuditLogEntity.java` — JPA entity for audit log\n  - `AuditLogRepository.java` — Spring Data repository\n- DoD:\n  - Migration runs successfully on local DB\n  - All domain classes compile and have basic unit tests\n  - Repository can save and retrieve audit log entries\n- Boundaries:\n  - Only database and domain layer — no services or filters yet\n  - Do not modify existing tables\n- Priority: high\n- Blocking: true\n- deps: []\n- locks: []\n- Expected paths:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/`\n- Size budget:\n  - max_files: 10\n  - max_loc: 500\n- Commands:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\"`\n- Exit criteria:\n  - Migration applies without errors\n  - Unit tests pass for domain classes\n  - Repository integration test passes\n- Steps:\n  1. Create Liquibase changelog for rbac_audit_log table with indexes\n  2. Create Role enum with standard roles\n  3. Create ProfileIdentity value object with validation\n  4. Create Permission enum\n  5. Create RbacDecision record\n  6. Create AuditLogEntity JPA entity\n  7. Create AuditLogRepository interface\n  8. Write unit tests for domain classes\n  9. Write repository integration test\n- Tests:\n  - profile: targeted\n  - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\" --tests \"*Role*\"`\n  - filters: `AuditLogRepositoryTest`, `RoleTest`\n- Acceptance mapping: AC-2 (audit log structure), spec:data_model\n- Risks & mitigations:\n  - Risk: Migration conflicts with existing schema → Mitigation: Use separate rbac changelog file\n  - Risk: JSONB type not supported → Mitigation: Verify PostgreSQL version compatibility\n- Dependencies: PostgreSQL database, Liquibase\n\n### I2: RBAC WebFilter + Audit logging service (iteration_id: I2)\n- parent_iteration_id: I1\n- Goal: Implement RBAC WebFlux filter for mutation API protection and async audit logging\n- Outputs:\n  - `RbacWebFilter.java` — Main RBAC filter (Order: HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100)\n  - `AuditLogService.java` — Async audit logging service\n  - `RbacPathMatcher.java` — Path matching logic for protected routes\n  - `RbacProperties.java` — Configuration properties\n  - `RbacConfiguration.java` — Spring configuration\n- DoD:\n  - Filter intercepts POST/PUT/DELETE requests\n  - Filter returns 403 for unauthorized requests\n  - Audit log entries written for allowed and denied access\n  - Configuration loaded from application-rbac.yaml\n- Boundaries:\n  - No profile service integration yet — use mock/stub\n  - No caching yet\n  - Do not modify existing controllers\n- Priority: high\n- Blocking: true\n- deps: [I1]\n- locks: []\n- Expected paths:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/`\n- Size budget:\n  - max_files: 8\n  - max_loc: 800\n- Commands:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilterTest*\"`\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLogServiceTest*\"`\n- Exit criteria:\n  - Filter unit tests pass with mocked role service\n  - Audit log service writes entries asynchronously\n  - 403 responses include informative JSON error body\n- Steps:\n  1. Create RbacProperties configuration record\n  2. Create RbacConfiguration with path matcher bean\n  3. Create RbacPathMatcher with protected path rules\n  4. Create AuditLogService with async executor\n  5. Create RbacWebFilter with identity extraction\n  6. Implement mutation method detection (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n  7. Implement public path skipping\n  8. Implement 403 response with JSON body\n  9. Write comprehensive unit tests for filter\n  10. Write unit tests for audit log service\n- Tests:\n  - profile: targeted\n  - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilterTest*\"`\n  - filters: `shouldDenyPostWithoutRole`, `shouldAllowPostWithRole`, `shouldSkipGetRequests`\n- Acceptance mapping: AC-1 (403 for unauthorized), AC-2 (audit logging)\n- Risks & mitigations:\n  - Risk: Filter order conflicts with existing filters → Mitigation: Order HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100\n  - Risk: Async audit logging blocks request → Mitigation: Use fixed thread pool with error handling\n- Dependencies: I1 (domain model)\n\n### I3: Profile service integration + Role caching (iteration_id: I3)\n- parent_iteration_id: I2\n- Goal: Integrate with profile service for role resolution and implement Caffeine caching\n- Outputs:\n  - `ProfileClient.java` — WebClient for profile service API\n  - `ProfileResponse.java` — DTO for profile service response\n  - `ProfileRoleService.java` — Role resolution with Caffeine cache\n  - `application-rbac.yaml` — Configuration file\n- DoD:\n  - Profile client fetches roles from profile service\n  - Roles cached with 5-minute TTL\n  - Cache stats exposed\n  - Fail-closed behavior on profile service errors\n- Boundaries:\n  - Profile service URL configurable\n  - Cache size limited to 10,000 entries\n  - Do not implement cache invalidation yet (done in I5)\n- Priority: high\n- Blocking: true\n- deps: [I2]\n- locks: []\n- Expected paths:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/application-rbac.yaml`\n- Size budget:\n  - max_files: 6\n  - max_loc: 400\n- Commands:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleServiceTest*\"`\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileClientTest*\"`\n- Exit criteria:\n  - ProfileRoleServiceTest passes with mocked cache\n  - Cache hit/miss stats working\n  - Profile client timeout configured (2 seconds)\n- Steps:\n  1. Add Caffeine dependency to build.gradle if missing\n  2. Create ProfileResponse DTO\n  3. Create ProfileClient with WebClient\n  4. Create ProfileRoleService with Caffeine cache\n  5. Configure cache TTL (5 minutes) and max size (10,000)\n  6. Implement hasAnyRole method with cache lookup\n  7. Implement fail-closed on profile service errors\n  8. Create application-rbac.yaml with configuration\n  9. Write unit tests for ProfileRoleService\n  10. Write integration tests for ProfileClient\n- Tests:\n  - profile: targeted\n  - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleServiceTest*\"`\n  - filters: `shouldCacheRoles`, `shouldFailClosedOnError`, `shouldExpireAfterTtl`\n- Acceptance mapping: AC-4 (P95 latency ≤ 10ms via caching)\n- Risks & mitigations:\n  - Risk: Profile service unavailable → Mitigation: Fail-closed, return empty roles (deny access)\n  - Risk: Cache stale data → Mitigation: 5min TTL acceptable for this use case\n- Dependencies: I2 (RBAC filter), Caffeine cache\n\n### I4: Frontend SSE integration + useRoleGuard hook (iteration_id: I4)\n- parent_iteration_id: I3\n- Goal: Implement frontend role synchronization via SSE and create useRoleGuard hook\n- Outputs:\n  - `useRoleGuard.ts` — React hook for role checking with SSE subscription\n  - `RoleGuard.tsx` — Component for conditional rendering based on roles\n  - Modified `profileStore.ts` — Add SSE subscription and roleVersion\n  - Modified `AdminRoles.tsx` — Use useRoleGuard hook\n- DoD:\n  - useRoleGuard subscribes to SSE role-events endpoint\n  - Hook updates when roles change via SSE\n  - RoleGuard component conditionally renders children\n  - AdminRoles page uses hook instead of inline checks\n- Boundaries:\n  - Extend existing SSE infrastructure (subscribeToFlowEvents pattern)\n  - Zustand store persists role state\n  - Do not modify other pages yet\n- Priority: high\n- Blocking: true\n- deps: [I3]\n- locks: []\n- Expected paths:\n  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts`\n  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx`\n  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n- Size budget:\n  - max_files: 4\n  - max_loc: 300\n- Commands:\n  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n  - `npm run build` (verify no TypeScript errors)\n- Exit criteria:\n  - useRoleGuard tests pass\n  - TypeScript compilation successful\n  - Hook correctly derives hasRole, hasAnyRole, hasAllRoles, isAdmin\n- Steps:\n  1. Add roleVersion and lastRoleSync to ProfileStoreState\n  2. Add subscribeToRoleChanges method to profileStore\n  3. Create useRoleGuard hook with SSE subscription\n  4. Implement hasRole, hasAnyRole, hasAllRoles, isAdmin helpers\n  5. Create RoleGuard component\n  6. Create AdminGuard component\n  7. Refactor AdminRoles.tsx to use useRoleGuard\n  8. Write unit tests for useRoleGuard hook\n  9. Verify SSE connection cleanup on unmount\n- Tests:\n  - profile: targeted\n  - tasks: `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n  - filters: `should update when roles change`, `should subscribe on mount`, `should cleanup on unmount`\n- Acceptance mapping: AC-3 (frontend updates within 5 seconds)\n- Risks & mitigations:\n  - Risk: SSE connection memory leak → Mitigation: Proper cleanup in useEffect return\n  - Risk: Zustand state not updating → Mitigation: Use roleVersion to trigger re-renders\n- Dependencies: I3 (backend role resolution), existing SSE infrastructure\n\n### I5: SSE endpoint + Role events (iteration_id: I5)\n- parent_iteration_id: I4\n- Goal: Implement backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications and role assignment service\n- Outputs:\n  - `RoleEventService.java` — SSE event management with Sinks.Many\n  - `RoleEventsController.java` — SSE endpoint /api/profiles/role-events\n  - `RoleAssignmentService.java` — Role assignment with cache invalidation and events\n  - `RoleChangeEvent.java` — Event record for role changes\n- DoD:\n  - SSE endpoint accepts namespace, reference, channel, token params\n  - Role change events broadcast to connected clients\n  - Cache invalidated on role assignment/revocation\n  - Audit log written for GRANT/REVOKE operations\n- Boundaries:\n  - Reuse existing SSE pattern from flow events\n  - Heartbeat every 30 seconds\n  - Proper cleanup on disconnect\n- Priority: medium\n- Blocking: false\n- deps: [I4]\n- locks: []\n- Expected paths:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n- Size budget:\n  - max_files: 5\n  - max_loc: 400\n- Commands:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEventsControllerTest*\"`\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleAssignmentServiceTest*\"`\n- Exit criteria:\n  - SSE endpoint tests pass\n  - Role assignment service tests pass\n  - End-to-end test: role change → SSE notification received\n- Steps:\n  1. Create RoleChangeEvent record\n  2. Create RoleEventService with subscriber management\n  3. Create RoleEventsController with SSE endpoint\n  4. Implement heartbeat flux (30s interval)\n  5. Create RoleAssignmentService\n  6. Implement assignRole with cache invalidation\n  7. Implement revokeRole with cache invalidation\n  8. Integrate audit logging for GRANT/REVOKE\n  9. Write controller tests for SSE endpoint\n  10. Write service tests for role assignment\n- Tests:\n  - profile: full\n  - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEvent*\" --tests \"*RoleAssignment*\"`\n  - filters: `shouldBroadcastRoleChange`, `shouldInvalidateCacheOnAssign`\n- Acceptance mapping: AC-3 (live role sync), AC-2 (audit for GRANT/REVOKE)\n- Risks & mitigations:\n  - Risk: Memory leak from stale subscribers → Mitigation: doOnCancel/doOnTerminate cleanup\n  - Risk: SSE backpressure → Mitigation: onBackpressureBuffer strategy\n- Dependencies: I4 (frontend SSE integration)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:NEXT_3\n> 3 ближайших implement‑чекбокса. Pointer list: 1–2 строки и `ref:` на детализацию.\n- [ ] I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model — Create rbac_audit_log table and domain classes (ref: iteration_id=I1)\n- [ ] I2: RBAC WebFilter + Audit logging service — Implement WebFlux filter for mutation API protection (ref: iteration_id=I2)\n- [ ] I3: Profile service integration + Role caching — Integrate profile client with Caffeine cache (ref: iteration_id=I3)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:OUT_OF_SCOPE_BACKLOG\n> Побочные идеи/задачи, которые НЕ входят в текущий work_item (без расширения scope).\n- [ ] Redis distributed cache for roles (instead of Caffeine) — source: research\n- [ ] WebSocket alternative to SSE — source: spec (outdated)\n- [ ] Role management UI — source: prd (non-goal)\n- [ ] Audit log archival to cold storage — source: plan (future enhancement)\n- [ ] Multi-tenant RBAC scope — source: prd (non-goal)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:HANDOFF_INBOX\n> Сюда падают задачи из Research/Review/QA (с source: aidd/reports/...).\n\n<!-- handoff:manual start -->\n<!-- handoff:manual end -->\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:QA_TRACEABILITY\n> AC → check → result → evidence.\n- AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users → RbacWebFilterTest → not-verified → aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n- AC-2: All role operations logged to rbac_audit_log → AuditLogServiceTest → not-verified → aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change → useRoleGuard.test.ts + e2e → not-verified → aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n- AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS → Performance test → not-verified → aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:CHECKLIST\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_SPEC\n- [x] PRD: Status READY (и нет незакрытых blocker вопросов)\n- [x] Research: Status reviewed\n- [x] Plan: существует и валиден\n- [x] Review Spec: Plan Review READY + PRD Review READY\n- [ ] Spec interview (optional): spec устарел (использует WebSocket вместо SSE) — не требуется\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_IMPLEMENT\n- [ ] Реализован функционал для checkbox #1 из AIDD:NEXT_3 (I1)\n- [ ] Добавлены/обновлены тесты по плану\n- [ ] Обновлён AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK (scope + test policy)\n- [ ] Обновлён AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION (если менялась тестовая тактика)\n- [ ] Прогресс отмечен (см. AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG)\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_REVIEW\n- [ ] Reviewer: замечания добавлены в tasklist (handoff)\n- [ ] Требуемость тестов выставлена (если используете reviewer marker)\n- [ ] Изменения соответствуют plan/PRD (нет лишнего)\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_QA\n- [ ] QA: AIDD:ACCEPTANCE проверены (traceability)\n- [ ] QA report сохранён (aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json)\n- [ ] Known issues задокументированы\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_RELEASE\n- [ ] Release notes / changelog (если нужно)\n- [ ] Deploy на стенд (env + версия + время)\n- [ ] Smoke / e2e (если есть)\n- [ ] Мониторинг/алерты/дашборды проверены\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_POST_RELEASE\n- [ ] Rollback plan проверен (если релевантно)\n- [ ] Метрики успеха/guardrails собраны\n- [ ] Техдолг/следующие шаги заведены\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG\n> Мини‑лог: фиксируй кратко, обновляй после каждой итерации.\n> Формат записи:\n> `- YYYY-MM-DD source=implement id=I4 kind=iteration hash=abc123 link=aidd/reports/tests/<ticket>/TST-001.jsonl msg=short-note`\n> `- YYYY-MM-DD source=review id=review:F6 kind=handoff hash=def456 link=aidd/reports/reviewer/<ticket>/TST-001.json msg=blocked`\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:HOW_TO_UPDATE\n- Правило итерации: **1 чекбокс** (или 2 тесно связанных) — затем Stop.\n- Отмечайте чекбоксы так:\n  - `- [x] I1: <title> (iteration_id: I1) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n  - `- [x] <handoff title> (id: review:F6) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n- После каждого [x] обновляй `AIDD:NEXT_3` (pointer list) и добавляй запись в `AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG`.\n- Если меняешь тестовый профиль/команды — обнови `AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`.\n- Если обновили spec — запусти `/feature-dev-aidd:tasks-new` для синхронизации tasklist.\n- Логи/stacktrace не вставлять в tasklist — только ссылки на `aidd/reports/**`.\n"}}],"model"