{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_HOc4L8tv12ParMsrGw0WExyE","type":"tool_result","content":"[Context GC] Full output saved to: /Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/logs/bash-20260318-145856.log\n[Context GC] Showing last 400 lines:\n---\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\nStatus: READY\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nOwner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\nPRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\nPlan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\nResearch: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\nReports:\n  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n---\n\n# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nStage: tasklist\nStatus: READY\n\n### TL;DR\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n\n### Scope & boundaries\n- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n- Integrations / dependencies:\n  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n\n### Decisions & defaults (living)\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n\n### Test policy (iteration budget)\n- Cadence: checkpoint\n- Profile: targeted\n- Tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`, `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Filters: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Budget minutes: 10\n- Known flaky / failing: none\n\n### Commands quickstart (copy/paste)\n- Format: cmd\n- Tests (manual): `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*Rbac*\"`, `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Run/Dev: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:bootRun`, `npm run dev` (frontend)\n- DB migration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n\n### Open questions / blockers\n- None — all questions resolved via PRD decisions Q1-Q5\n\n### Blockers summary (handoff)\n- None\n\n### References\n- Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (OUTDATED — uses WebSocket, follow Plan for SSE)\n- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md (Status: READY, Q5=B polling but Plan uses SSE)\n- Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n- Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md (Status: READY, source of truth for implementation)\n- Reports:\n  - review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  - reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  - qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:SPEC_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (status: draft — OUTDATED)\n\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement on mutation APIs with auditable role operations and SSE-based frontend synchronization\n- Non-goals:\n  - UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n  - Migration of historical access logs\n  - Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n  - WebSocket (Spec says WebSocket, but Plan uses SSE — follow Plan)\n- Key decisions:\n  - Backend: Custom WebFlux filter for RBAC (no Spring Security)\n  - Auth: X-Profile-Key header-based identity extraction\n  - Frontend: React + Zustand (not Redux as in Spec)\n  - Session Sync: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — NOT WebSocket, NOT Polling\n  - Cache: Caffeine with 5min TTL\n  - Audit: PostgreSQL table `rbac_audit_log` with JSONB metadata\n- Risks:\n  - R-001: Profile service unavailable → Circuit breaker, fail-closed, cache roles\n  - R-002: Cache stale roles after assignment → Cache invalidation on role change\n  - R-003: SSE connection memory leak → Proper cleanup on disconnect\n  - R-004: Audit log write failures → Async logging, error queue\n  - R-005: RBAC filter performance degradation → Caffeine cache, async audit\n  - R-006: Breaking change to existing APIs → Feature flags, audit-only mode first\n  - R-007: Component scan misses RBAC beans → Add to all profile configs\n  - R-008: Missing profile service integration → Define contract or implement local role storage\n\n## AIDD:TEST_STRATEGY\n- Unit:\n  - Scope: RBAC middleware logic, role caching, audit log formatting, useRoleGuard hook\n  - Files: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Integration:\n  - Scope: RBAC filter + profile service client, audit log DB writes, SSE endpoint connection handling\n  - Files: `RbacIntegrationTest`, `RoleEventsControllerTest`\n- Contract:\n  - Scope: API response schemas (403 format), SSE event format\n  - Files: Contract tests for `/api/profiles/role-events` endpoint\n- E2E/Stand:\n  - Critical paths:\n    - flow.admin-change-role: Admin assigns role → user receives SSE update\n    - flow.unauthorized-access: User attempts restricted action → 403 + audit log\n    - flow.live-session-update: Role change propagates to frontend within 5 seconds\n- Test data:\n  - Fixtures: Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions, regular user with limited role, user with missing headers\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION\n> Конкретные команды/фильтры запуска (execution‑уровень).\n- profile: targeted\n- tasks:\n  - Backend: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n  - Frontend: `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n  - Integration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacIntegrationTest*\"`\n- filters:\n  - `RbacWebFilterTest` — filter logic tests\n  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest` — caching and role resolution tests\n  - `AuditLogServiceTest` — audit logging tests\n  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts` — frontend hook tests","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"c68bb6c6-812e-4455-a563-5cf6221356b8","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"[Context GC] Full output saved to: /Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/logs/bash-20260318-145856.log\n[Context GC] Showing last 400 lines:\n---\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\nStatus: READY\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nOwner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\nPRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\nPlan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\nResearch: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\nReports:\n  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n  review_report: aidd/rep