{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_B475rSgZYXQROyetgx7gbSNz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the validation delegates to `aidd_runtime.tasklist_validate.check_tasklist_text`. The issue is with parsing the iteration blocks. Let me look at what format the validator expects. The issue seems to be that the DoD field might not be found correctly due to how the block is parsed.\n\nLooking at the `extract_field_value` function (line 339), it looks for patterns like `^\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?{field}\\s*:\\s*(.*)$`. This means it's looking for fields at the start of a line with `- Field: value` format.\n\nBut in my tasklist, the fields are nested under the iteration checkbox with 2-space indentation. Let me check the block parsing more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at `split_iteration_blocks`, it seems to collect lines after the header checkbox line. The issue is that `extract_field_value` might be looking at the wrong indent level.\n\nLet me run the check with `--fix` to see if normalization helps.","signature":""}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":77296,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":77296,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"93f73f8c-629c-4315-891e-89cb20c2061d"}
