{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_HVdrKdOxtJO06J9FS1DWzIJR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The DoD field is clearly there in the file. The issue must be in how the validator parses it. Looking at the `extract_field_value` function, it expects the pattern:\n```\n^\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?{field}\\s*:\\s*(.*)$\n```\n\nThis should match `- DoD:` at the start of a line. But the lines have 2-space indentation. Let me check if the issue is the block parsing.\n\nActually, looking at `split_iteration_blocks`, it collects lines after the header checkbox. But it seems like it might be stopping early or the block content isn't being passed correctly to the field extractor.\n\nLet me try a simpler format for DoD - as a single line field instead of a list.","signature":""}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":79275,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":79275,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"561ccae1-39ce-487b-83e5-341049316200"}
