{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_iP6huujZa4llNuD8kvfOv87y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→Ticket: TST-001\n     3→Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     4→Status: READY\n     5→Updated: 2026-03-18\n     6→Owner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\n     7→PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n     8→Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\n     9→Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n    10→Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\n    11→Reports:\n    12→  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n    13→  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n    14→  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n    15→  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n    19→\n    20→> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n    21→> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n    24→Updated: 2026-03-18\n    25→Ticket: TST-001\n    26→Stage: tasklist\n    27→Status: READY\n    28→\n    29→### TL;DR\n    30→- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n    31→- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n    32→- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n    33→- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n    34→\n    35→### Scope & boundaries\n    36→- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n    37→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n    38→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n    39→  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n    40→  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n    41→  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n    42→  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n    43→- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n    44→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n    45→  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n    46→  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n    47→  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n    48→- Integrations / dependencies:\n    49→  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n    50→  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n    51→  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n    52→  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n    53→\n    54→### Decisions & defaults (living)\n    55→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n    56→- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n    57→- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n    58→- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n    59→\n    60→### Test policy (iteration budget)\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bb52f18-577c-4498-9d63-c3d743a62879","uuid":"8ea5d94c-0d84-445f-8450-f10fc4ba232f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md","content":"---\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\nStatus: READY\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nOwner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\nPRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\nPlan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\nResearch: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\nReports:\n  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n---\n\n# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nStage: tasklist\nStatus: READY\n\n### TL;DR\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n\n### Scope & boundaries\n- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n- Integrations / dependencies:\n  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n\n### Decisions & defaults (living)\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n\n### Test policy (iteration budget)","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":495}}}
